; FILED: do-loop composition is broken two ways:
;   (a) nested do: inner/outer interaction loses iterations
;       native: 000102   vm: 00
;   (b) do with `when` in the body: the loop variable stops advancing and
;       the VM spins FOREVER printing the first iteration's output.
; Only (a) is active below; (b) is left commented so this repro terminates.
(do ((i 0 (+ i 1))) ((= i 3))
  (do ((j 0 (+ j 1))) ((= j 2))
    (display (* i j))))
(newline)
; (b) infinite loop — uncomment to reproduce:
; (do ((i 0 (+ i 1))) ((= i 3)) (when (> i 0) (display i)))
